      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>Mr. John F. Banks became principal of the Christiansburg
         Industrial Institute in 1949. Banks was a graduate of
         Wilberforce University in Ohio and Hampton Institute. During
         his tenure the United States Supreme Court ruled that school
         segregation based on color was unconstitutional. Nevertheless,
         it was not until the 1960's when Montgomery County began
         efforts to dismantle their dual system of education. Mr. Banks
         was the last principal of Christiansburg. The school closed in
         1966.</p>
         <p>Other material about Christiansburg may be found in: The
         Amanda DeHart Papers Acc. # 1988-61, The Christiansburg Alumni
         Association Papers Acc. # 1988-62, The Virginia
         Inter-Scholastic Association Papers Acc. # 1969-37, and The
         Virginia Teacher Association Papers Acc. # 1969-14, all
         located at Virginia State University.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Official records and photographs documenting some of the
         programs and activities at the Christiansburg Industrial
         Institute.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement>
         <head>Series Description</head>
         <p>Series I. Printed Catalogs and bulletins of the
         Christiansburg Industrial Institution</p>
         <p>Series II. Photographs Photographs showing programs,
         buildings, and activities at Christiansburg</p>
         <p>Series III. Artifacts Christiansburg Seal</p>
      </arrangement>
